  <description type="morphology">Heads in pyramidal paniculiform arrays, proximal branches arching to recurved. 2n = 18, 36, 54.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering Aug–Oct.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Dry to moist sandy and gravelly soils, meadows, along streams and rivers;</description>
  <description type="elevation">0–2900+ m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Alta., B.C., Man., Sask.; Ariz., Colo., Idaho, Mont., Nev., N.Mex., Utah, Wash., Wyo.</description>
